Additionally, it could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a practical attack method using differential evolution. The paper also discusses the security aspect of DNNs, which could place it under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of differential evolution as an optimization algorithm could also place it under the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
